<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,261,850]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis box="[197,340,298,323]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">Coloration.</emphasis>
Pale brown. Head (
<figureCitation box="[587,656,298,324]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,256,795,819]" captionTargetBox="[269,1324,200,761]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[262,1324,184,774]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Pedionis dorsal and lateral habitus. A &amp; B, Pedionis (Pedionis) lii sp. nov.; C &amp; D, Pedionis (Pedionis) spinata sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195496/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
Fig. 
<number box="[645,656,298,324]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A) with numerous pale and dark brown spots; facial calli pale; anteclypeus dark brown. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[613,702,336,362]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,256,795,819]" captionTargetBox="[269,1324,200,761]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[262,1324,184,774]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Pedionis dorsal and lateral habitus. A &amp; B, Pedionis (Pedionis) lii sp. nov.; C &amp; D, Pedionis (Pedionis) spinata sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195496/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
Figs. 
<number box="[686,702,336,362]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A – B) with numerous dark brown and pale brown spots. Scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[289,356,373,399]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,256,795,819]" captionTargetBox="[269,1324,200,761]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[262,1324,184,774]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Pedionis dorsal and lateral habitus. A &amp; B, Pedionis (Pedionis) lii sp. nov.; C &amp; D, Pedionis (Pedionis) spinata sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195496/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
Fig. 
<number box="[345,356,373,399]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A) darker than pronotum with pale brown basal triangles. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[1190,1257,373,399]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,256,795,819]" captionTargetBox="[269,1324,200,761]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[262,1324,184,774]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Pedionis dorsal and lateral habitus. A &amp; B, Pedionis (Pedionis) lii sp. nov.; C &amp; D, Pedionis (Pedionis) spinata sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195496/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
Fig. 
<number box="[1246,1257,373,399]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B) brown with oblique fenestra across midlength hyaline, spot in each subapical cells hyaline, venation dark brown with white spots. Legs brown, apices of femora, last tarsomeres ochraceous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,261,850]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis box="[197,350,485,510]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">Morphology.</emphasis>
Body stout. Face (
<figureCitation box="[578,648,485,511]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,256,1979,2003]" captionTargetBox="[255,1330,1711,1954]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[251,1335,1704,1959]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Facial aspect of Pedionis. A, Pedionis (Pedionis) lii sp. nov.; B, Pedionis (Pedionis) spinata sp. nov.; C, Pedionis (Pedionis) yunnana sp. nov., male; D, Pedionis (Pedionis) yunnana sp. nov., female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195498/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
Fig. 
<number box="[634,648,485,511]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A), slightly convex in lateral view. Eyes slightly prominent. 
<collectingCountry box="[1376,1436,485,511]" name="India" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibial spinulation R 
<number box="[375,383,538,552]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" value="1.0">1</number>
<number box="[391,422,522,548]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" value="15.0">15</number>
, R 
<number box="[454,462,538,552]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" value="2.0">2</number>
<number box="[470,486,522,548]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" value="9.0">9</number>
, R 
<number box="[518,526,538,552]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" value="3.0">3</number>
<number box="[533,550,522,548]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" value="5.0">5</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,261,850]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis box="[197,380,563,588]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygophore (
<figureCitation box="[534,606,562,588]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,255,1762,1786]" captionTargetBox="[261,1322,922,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[253,1334,904,1741]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pedionis (Pedionis) lii sp. nov. A, pygofer, subgenital plates and valve, lateral view; B, style, lateral view; C, aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; D, aedeagus and dorsal connective, caudal view; E, connective, lateral view; F, connective, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195499/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
Fig. 
<number box="[591,606,562,588]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A) triangular, in lateral view, caudal margin serrate dorsally and with teeth subdorsally. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[594,669,600,626]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,255,1762,1786]" captionTargetBox="[261,1322,922,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[253,1334,904,1741]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pedionis (Pedionis) lii sp. nov. A, pygofer, subgenital plates and valve, lateral view; B, style, lateral view; C, aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; D, aedeagus and dorsal connective, caudal view; E, connective, lateral view; F, connective, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195499/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
Fig. 
<number box="[653,669,600,626]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A) narrow and long with marginal setae. Style and connective similar to those in 
<taxonomicName authority="Distant" authorityName="Distant" box="[378,696,637,663]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pedionis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="garuda">
<emphasis box="[378,577,638,663]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">Pedionis garuda</emphasis>
(Distant)
</taxonomicName>
. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[843,927,637,663]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,255,1762,1786]" captionTargetBox="[261,1322,922,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[253,1334,904,1741]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pedionis (Pedionis) lii sp. nov. A, pygofer, subgenital plates and valve, lateral view; B, style, lateral view; C, aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; D, aedeagus and dorsal connective, caudal view; E, connective, lateral view; F, connective, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195499/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
Figs. 
<number box="[912,927,637,663]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
C, D) broader basally and then narrowed, sinuately curved near apical 
<number box="[502,558,674,700]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" value="0.27">0.27</number>
, apex with lateral flanges, shaft produced into pointed structure at apex beyond gonopore; preatrium well developed; dorsal connective elaborate, distal arm more or less of uniform width, bent near base and also near apex (
<figureCitation box="[655,728,749,775]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,255,1762,1786]" captionTargetBox="[261,1322,922,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[253,1334,904,1741]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pedionis (Pedionis) lii sp. nov. A, pygofer, subgenital plates and valve, lateral view; B, style, lateral view; C, aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; D, aedeagus and dorsal connective, caudal view; E, connective, lateral view; F, connective, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195499/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
Fig. 
<number box="[712,728,749,775]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
C), margins smooth except minutely serrated mesal margin near apex,.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,261,850]" box="[197,408,824,850]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis box="[197,293,824,849]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">Female.</emphasis>
Unkown.
</paragraph>
